This paper deals with the task of automatic tagging of movies based on their plot synopses. This involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper also deals with the analysis of visual and emotional experiences in movies, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.MM.
